casebody.data:
Phillip H. GEORGE, Plaintiff in Error, v. UNITED STATES, Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. November 29, 1927. No. 5065. Don A. Bliss, of San Antonio, Tex., for plaintiff in error. John D. Hartman, U. S. Atty., of San Antonio, Tex. (Russell B. Wine, Asst. U. S. Atty., of San Antonio, Tex., on the brief), for the United States.

Before WALKER, BRYAN, and FOSTER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
